<Defs>

	<ThingDef ParentName="AnimalThingBase">
		<defName>BMT_Centrosaurus</defName>
		<label>centrosaurus</label>
		<description>While fairly small for a dinosaur, they live in huge herds making them a dangerous animal to hunt. They are highly variable, with their frills changing shape as they age and having nose horns that can point forwards or backwards depending on the individual.\n\nScientific name: Centrosaurus apertus (Open pointed lizard) \n\nThe name refers to the dinosaur's frill, which has holes in and small spines around the edge. The nose horn was discovered after the animal had been named.</description>
